org.jbox2d.common

Class Vec2

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jbox2d.common.Vec2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Vec2
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A 2-dimensional vector, expressing a directional quantity in world space. A vector can be viewed in two ways:
    • as a pair of numbers (Cartesian coordinates) specifying a position in space:
      • the x-coordinate, measured from left to right, and
      • the y-coordinate, measured from top to bottom, or
    • as a line segment of a particular length and direction.
    See Also:

      • mul

        public final Vec2 mul(float a)
        Return this vector multiplied by a number; does not alter this vector. Geometrically, the result is a vector in the same dircetion, but with its length multiplied by a. (So if a is negative, the result will be a vector in the opposite direction.)
        Parameters:
        a - number to multiply the vector by
        Returns:
        a new vector obtained by multiplying each component of this one by a
